# Frontend production build template.
# Copy this file to .env.production before running `npm run build`.
# Do not commit real environment values if they contain private endpoints.
#
# Browser deployment on the same public origin:
# If the frontend is served from the same host as the API, such as:
#   https://app.example.com
#   https://app.example.com/api/...
# then leave VITE_API_URL unset so the app uses relative /api paths.
#
# Cross-origin browser API deployment:
# If the frontend origin differs from the API origin, set the HTTPS API origin
# without a trailing slash and make sure the backend FRONTEND_ORIGIN allows it.
# VITE_API_URL=https://api.example.com
#
# Capacitor/native builds:
# Native builds use this fixed HTTPS API origin and do not allow changing the API
# host from the login screen.
# VITE_NATIVE_API_URL=https://api.example.com
#
# CDN / direct-media deployments:
# If media or encrypted DM attachments are served from a CDN or public object
# storage domain, allow only the exact HTTPS base path prefix used for those
# objects. Root origins such as https://cdn.example.com/ are rejected by the app.
# VITE_ALLOWED_MEDIA_BASE_URLS=https://cdn.example.com/media/
# VITE_ALLOWED_DM_ATTACHMENT_BASE_URLS=https://cdn.example.com/dm/
